news.title: No action against Bagmane Tech Park till law is followed: Karnataka HC
news.para: The judge, while disposing of Bagmane's petition, directed the authorities to give a copy of the survey report to the petitioner and provide an opportunity of hearing and then take action in the matter.

news.title: Adani names son to run cement firms; injects Rs 20,000 crore in Ambuja Cement
news.para: Adani group announced the completion of the acquisition of Ambuja Cements and ACC for a total consideration of USD 6.5 billion which includes the buyout of Swiss major Holcim's state in the two firms and subsequent open offers to minority shareholders.

news.title: Registration expires, Haryana RERA bans sale & purchase in two projects
news.para: H-Rera has also served show-cause notices to two other projects for not completing the registration process, which is mandatory.

news.title: La Residentia Developers' office sealed for not paying Rs 15 crore recovery dues
news.para: La Residentia, launched in 2010, had a 2014 deadline. While some towers in the society are complete, the developer has not handed over all the flats in those; others are still under construction.

news.title: Nykaa E-Retail leases over 55,000 sq ft office space in Mumbai's Lower Parel
news.para: The company, listed on stock exchanges as FSN E-Commerce Ventures, will be paying rentals of Rs 69 lakh per month, taking its total payout to Rs 41.40 crore excluding the rental escalation. The agreement includes a clause to escalate lease rentals by 15% after the first 36 months.

news.title: China's property sector contracts further with prices, sales falling
news.para: Once a key driver of economic growth, China's property market has lurched from crisis to crisis since the summer of 2020 after regulators stepped in to cut excess leverage at developers.

news.title: Eldeco, HDFC Capital form Rs 350 crore fund for housing projects
news.para: Earlier, Eldeco Group had partnered with HDFC Capital Affordable Real Estate Fund 1 (H-CARE 1) to set up a Rs 150 crore platform for the development of low-rise and plotted development projects.

news.title: Chandigarh: 600 duplex houses face the axe in Sector 41
news.para: Yashpal Garg, CEO, CHB, said, "We have started issuing the final demolition notices to the allottees of the dwelling units. So far, more than 400 notices have been issued, and more are under process."

news.title: Chandigarh to sell five-star hotel site in Sector 34
news.para: A five-star hotel site spread over 3.5 acres adjoining the road dividing sectors 33 and 34 is ready to be offered for sale at probably more than Rs 500 crore though the reserve price is not yet finalised.

news.title: Jaipur: JMC-Heritage to take strict action against 53 illegal buildings
news.para: The commissioner directed officials to take immediate action against 53 illegal constructions identified by the vigilance branch of the corporation along with submitting an inspection report every day all the deputy commissioners.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM says Tidel Park to be set up in Madurai
news.para: Addressing the south zone industrial conference in Madurai, Stalin hoped that the proposed Tidel Park would provide the infrastructure for information technology and FinTech companies.

news.title: About 100 buildings near ASI sites in Ahmedabad under CBI scanner
news.para: A probe by the CBI has alleged that some civic officials in connivance with ASI and NMA officials granted NOCs to private persons to construct residential and commercial buildings around centrally protected monuments in the Walled City in exchange for monetary favours.

news.title: Gurugram: New billing system to delink power bills from backup and upkeep fees
news.para: Under single-point connections, DHBVN prepares one bill for the entire society, the developer or the RWA then prepares individual bills for the flats, clubbing backup and upkeep charges with the same.

news.title: MHA seeks three months to decide on allowing conversion to freehold in Chandigarh
news.para: "This being a major policy decision, the matter is being considered according to the established legal procedures and consultation with all stakeholders concerned," the MHA and UT have submitted.

news.title: Petition in Orissa HC says RERA has not heard a single case since 2017
news.para: The ORERA order said: "In case of delivery of possession, the civil court is well equipped to enforce an order through the process of the court. The authority does not possess the power of a magistrate to direct a party to serve civil prison in case of violation."
